      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TUFFASOLDBOOTS (5) has been good from tough barriers of late. Won from the second line at Canberra last month then drew out but worked home in good style to finish a head from the winner in second at this circuit and distance last week. Draws a couple of spots lower. Good enough to win a race of this calibre. There was merit in the latest effort of CARMEN ON BLING (6) when beaten 5.4 metres at this circuit and distance. Draws wider but with even luck he can be prominent. WEENEEDDREAMS (3) draws well and must be considered having finished third in both outings since a fresh win at Leeton. BARWEN STORM (8) has claims after he came from a similar draw and finished third here three weeks ago.",
